    <bioghist encodinganalog="5450_">
      <head>Biographical Note</head>
      <p>Louisa Stone was born on March 17, 1838 in Missouri. She married Samuel King and the couple
        had 11 children. In 1864 the King family moved to Alder Gulch, Montana, and afterwards to
        the outskirts of Bozeman where Samuel died in 1873. In April 1875 Louisa married Mark Burton
        and the couple lived on the King property until Mark's death in 1883. In partnership with
        her son, Granville A. King, Louisa rented pasture at her farm to area stockgrowers and sold
        garden produce. She died on January 8, 1913.</p>
    </bioghist>
    <scopecontent encodinganalog="5202_">
      <p>The Louisa Burton Ledger lists transactions from 1889 to 1895. Information includes the
        surname of the stockgrower, the number and dates of cattle or horses pastured, and prices
        charged. There are also brief household account entries, and some data on vegetable sales to
        Bozeman residents.</p>
    </scopecontent>
